  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Deborah Weston is to tell Mr. E. [John F. Emerson] that Maria Weston Chapman is &quot;entirely ready &amp; happy to assume any responsibility about the publication of the letter, that he thinks right.&quot; Maria W. Chapman believes that &quot;he would not wish to appear to Mr. P [Amos Augustus Phelps] in any other light than as the exposer of that letter.&quot; Caroline Weston is back from Philadelphia. Chapman comments: &quot;L[ucretia] Mott all right. Penn. will sympathise with us.&quot;</subfield>
